{
  "texts": [
    "The binned spectrum shown in Fig. 3 contrasts expectations from the 324k models (green) to the measured correlated signal in DR2new (orange).",
    "The two sets of violin plots are in good agreement in the few lowest frequency bins, where measurements are the most constraining.",
    "Note that the model prediction distributions are highly non-Gaussian and asymmetric, with long tails extending upwards.",
    "This is due to the fact that sparse very massive/nearby binaries can sometimes produce exceptionally loud signals, as illustrated by the 100 individual GWBs overplotted to the violins.",
    "In fact, this might explain the extra power measured in the 4th and, most strikingly, in the 9th lowest bins compared to the bulk of the model predictions."
  ]
}